cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.GR, cs.PF, cs.MS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing an efficient algorithm for answering shortest-path queries in planar graphs.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the algorithm is implemented on a multi-node CPU/GPU cluster.
- cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is a possible category as planar graphs are often used in computer graphics applications.
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm on GPU-accelerated architectures.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves the development and implementation of a mathematical algorithm.
